<item>
            <title>[PPLNS-7738] Configure a lakehouse-copy-file job to unpack/copy Callminer export files from holding to landing</title>
                <link>https://theverygroup.atlassian.net/browse/PPLNS-7738</link>
                <project id="20015" key="PPLNS">Data Enablement</project>
                    <description>&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name="Description"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Description&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Callminer BulkAPI export jobs will push files to &lt;/p&gt;
{env}-lakehouse-holding-zone which will need to be unpacked and copied to {env}
&lt;p&gt;-lakehouse-landing-zone before they are ingested. A lakehouse-copy-file task can be configured to do this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The structure of the Callminer output however can't be fully unpacked by the lakehouse-copy-file process in its current form. The output consists of a main zip file containing;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A Json file for each extracted data type containing info about the export such as the time period it covers and the number of records returned&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A csv.gz file for each extracted data type containing the exported records&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;It’s the zipped csv files which contain the records to be ingested. The lakehouse-copy-file process can unpack zipped files, but it can’t unpack zipped files nested within another zipped file. The process would have to be updated to allow this or a workaround would have to be implemented (e.g. unzip/copy the main zip file to an interim location and then unzip/copy the nested files to the landing location).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This task is to configure the lakehouse-copy-file job along with any update/workaround needed to unpack nested zip files.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;S3 Holding Zone bucket repo =&amp;gt; &lt;a href="https://git.tech.theverygroup.com/data/platform/lakehouse/s3/holding-zone/-/blob/master/tf/holding-zone-bucket.tf?ref_type=heads" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer"&gt;https://git.tech.theverygroup.com/data/platform/lakehouse/s3/holding-zone/-/blob/master/tf/holding-zone-bucket.tf?ref_type=heads&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;lakehouse-copy-file repo =&amp;gt; &lt;a href="https://git.tech.theverygroup.com/data/pipelines/lakehouse/jobs/lakehouse-copy-file" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer"&gt;https://git.tech.theverygroup.com/data/pipelines/lakehouse/jobs/lakehouse-copy-file&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;copy-task-lambda repo =&amp;gt; &lt;a href="https://git.tech.theverygroup.com/data/pipelines/lakehouse/jobs/copy-task-lambda" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer"&gt;https://git.tech.theverygroup.com/data/pipelines/lakehouse/jobs/copy-task-lambda&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name="FileOutput"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;File Output&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To provide the same information to customer care offered by the current process we will need to extract the below data types;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Contacts&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Categories&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Category_Components&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Scores&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Score_Indicators&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;This will give us an output that looks like the below;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;20260213_38ba7771-95fd-4800-98c3-019c57902b94.zip
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;38ba7771-95fd-4800-98c3-019c57902b94_Category_Components_Layout.json&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;38ba7771-95fd-4800-98c3-019c57902b94_Category_Components.csv.gz&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;38ba7771-95fd-4800-98c3-019c57902b94_Contacts_Layout.json&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;38ba7771-95fd-4800-98c3-019c57902b94_Contacts.csv.gz&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;38ba7771-95fd-4800-98c3-019c57902b94_Categories.json&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;38ba7771-95fd-4800-98c3-019c57902b94_Categories.csv.gz&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;38ba7771-95fd-4800-98c3-019c57902b94_Scores.json&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;38ba7771-95fd-4800-98c3-019c57902b94_Scores.csv.gz&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;38ba7771-95fd-4800-98c3-019c57902b94_Score_Indicators.json&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;38ba7771-95fd-4800-98c3-019c57902b94_Score_Indicators.csv.gz&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;




&lt;div class="panel" style="background-color: #deebff;border-width: 1px;"&gt;&lt;div class="panelContent" style="background-color: #deebff;"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The files needed for the ingestion will include at least those listed above. Some additional files may be added after discussions with Customer Care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;An example zip file can be found in a temporary S3 bucket here: &lt;a href="https://eu-west-1.console.aws.amazon.com/s3/object/dev-lakehouse-landing-zone?region=eu-west-1&amp;amp;prefix=callminer/temp/20260330_e7bfdc99-cca7-4056-a375-019d3e329eed.zip" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer"&gt;https://eu-west-1.console.aws.amazon.com/s3/object/dev-lakehouse-landing-zone?region=eu-west-1&amp;amp;prefix=callminer/temp/20260330_e7bfdc99-cca7-4056-a375-019d3e329eed.zip&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
